Most of the time in the trend for tweeting hilarious and occasionally controversial statements Elon Musk today replied to a tweet that 'Moody’s is irrelevant. But why again?On September 3 the CEO of Tesla Inc. gave a casual response to a series of tweets about Moody’s downgrading Tesla’s ratings. This is not the first time when Moody and Elon Musk have been in the news together. Earlier in 2018 Moody’s dropped the ratings of Tesla. This year in April they were planning to drop the ratings of Twitter when Musk was planning to acquire the social media platform.A famous financial YouTuber Dave Lee tagged Musk attaching an image that Alexandra Merz a Twitter user tweeted. Alexandra got a mail response from Rene one of the employees of Moody’s. Rene mailed the reasons for giving low ratings to Tesla Inc. and gave suggestions about how the ratings can be upgraded for the company.Mail body of Rene an employee at Moody’sShe says the following in the mail response:According to Moody if a company succeeds in improving its operations and diversifies it beyond its reliance on advertisements (which usually would generate around 90% of its revenue) it will be considered a positive credit.A. Twitter users laughed off at the response inviting a wave of users to flood the reply section. A user mockingly asked about Apple’s ratings while others lashed out asking if they would be teaching Musk about how to run a business. As a whole Elon simply tweeted Moody’s reply as IRRELEVANT. That is how Musk’s tweet once again became trending on Twitter.A. Moody’s Corporation is an American company specializing in financial services which was established in 1909 by John Moody. The company got listed in the Fortune 500 Companies in 2021.
